<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-11T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-11T17:00:00-05:00" n="32" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d32">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/2066: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                            to the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-11T18:00:00-04:00">March 11,
                                1942—6 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>162. Your 194, March 6, 3 p.m., and 195, March 7, 9 a.m. The Department has
                        found your reference telegrams most helpful and particularly appreciates
                        receiving the interpretative comment and constructive suggestions contained
                        therein. The Department is bringing your suggestions to the attention of the
                        governmental organs concerned.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>